@chapter Managing Toots

When you play in Tootsville, you'll take control of a Toot character
yourself. When you first sign in, you'll be guided through creating your
first Toot character.

If you later decide you want to create another one, perhaps for a family
member, you can also do so from the login screen.

@node
@section Creating a New Toot

Toot characters start off with a name and an appearance. We'll also give you
a few items with which to start your exploration.

Toot names are just like human names, but they all have to be unique. You
can join together word-parts with hyphens. Here are some Toot names:

@itemize
@item
Flora
@item
NullPointerException
@item
Codfish-Howie
@end itemize

If you really want to include a number, it has to be the last part of a
name. You can't name a Toot something like ``99luftballoons,'' but you could
name them ``Luftballoons-99'' or so.

Toot characters have some basic appearance settings, as well. You can choose
the base color of your Toot's skin, the color of the pads of their feet (and
``hands''), and the color of the pattern on their skin. You can also choose
what pattern they will have.

Once you've made these choices, you can immediately start playing as your
Toot character.


